<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>About half the time we would gain aggro for a brief period until the monk (who was 10 levels more than us) would gain it back.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
&quot;we&quot; would gain agro meant you two were ponging. Not a good thing. Melee has to run back and forth to regain the target, and he's not going to be pleased. Also, while he's chasing the target, he's not doing as much damage as if the target were stationary. If the cleric was going oom healing a monk that had 10 levels instead of you, then he wasn't the smartest cleric on the planet, because one ch and sit is tons more efficient than healing two wizards. <br>
<br>
Gaining agro is the worst possible thing a wizard can do on a raid, and once you get higher in levels, it will hurt you a lot in exp groups also.<br>
<br>
Another thing, stop chain stunning, because stuns are the highest agro spells we have; it may be a better idea to save stuns for interrupting gaters/casters. Replace the stuns with higher damage nukes.<br>
<br>
Learn to control agro by using concussion. You as a wizard, have the ability to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>never</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> get hit, if you don't want to, (in exp groups). If the healer has only one target to heal, he's happy. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Sage Flintnilf Ironori</b>

