If your healer spends more mana healing a tank, he is doing something wrong. Bigger heals tend to be more efficient than smaller heals and complete heal is most effective when it is being used to heal much larger amounts of hit points. Unless the caster can mitigate damage better and has more HP than the melees, he should not be getting hit at all.<br>
<br>
Also, like Flintnilf pointed out, you will soon be fighting mobs that will kill you pretty quick if you gain agro. If you manage to stay alive, now the healer is working twice as hard to keep the group alive. As wizards, our job is to do as much damage as possible without gaining agro. Sure, stuns have their place and uses, but if you are consistently getting agro using them, you are not using them properly. <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
<img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/Wandor_sig.jpg"><br>
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=312001"><b>Wandor</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=353608" target="_blank"><b>Wandorfu</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cryptixfractalshot>Cryptix Fractalshot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/03 3:05:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25965.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.winisp.net/nickreynolds/images/cryptface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wizards handle your aggro</span><hr size=1> I use stuns all the time, as it does save on cleric's mana, or more importantly it gives the complete heal a chance to land without needing a patch heal.<br>
<br>
I never mind taking agro when my epic rune takes all of the damage before I can concussion off my agro, but pissing off a cleric is also a bad thing to do.<br>
<br>
Using your stuns is less mana efficient than using your best mana / dmg spell to maximize your damage over time (and do this without taking agro).<br>
<br>
In the case you described, there are 3 ways of playing IMO. <br>
1) Efficient nukes, let the monk tank so the cleric only needs to heal him  (highest DPS, most efficient for you)<br>
2) Stuns with some nukes, help keep the cleric mana high for over pulls (lowers your DPS due to high mana cost of stuns)<br>
3) Efficient nukes with a few stuns, This is the way I play most of the time, I always ask an enchanter to tash on the pull so I can open with a stun.  If the stun is resisted than my epic rune eats the damage until the mob can be slowed.  If the stun does work than I just saved the group several seconds of damage from an unslowed mob.  I've gone several pulls in a row doing this without the MT needing a CH, and the enchanter never getting hit.  Your puller queue's off the clerics mana, and if you help preserve that, than your biggest worry is your own mana. <p>Cryptix Fractalshot<br>
Dark Elf Arcanist<br>
