<br>
One wizard demonstrated that he could lead off with stun and save the cleric mana from unslowed mobs banging on tanks, and it sounded very effective. I definately learned something from that. <br>
<br>
Another wizard suggested that if you don't get agro at some point, you're slacking on damage, and he may well be right, but I run oom chain casting with maximum mana regen quite often, and can go hours without gaining agro. <br>
<br>
A cleric asks me if i want a hp buff, and I'll tell him I'm not getting hit, do it only if it makes him feel better. I've never had any complaints about my dps, and I get asked to group as soon as I log on. I have 200+ AA's after skipping the 1st 3 months of POP, most of them by grouping, so i get lots of groups. <br>
<br>
I maintain that agro is controlled not by how <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>much</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you nuke, but <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>how</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you nuke. For instance, if you SOS- concussion- Ice spear, you can get agro, while if you Ice Spear-concussion-SOS you may <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> get agro.<br>
<br>
Depending on your tank, you may not even need to cast concussion at all. Or you may need to cast 2 or 3. <br>
<br>
One wizard will get agro without getting hit by carefully placing nukes at the right moment, that is also admirable. Another will save big nukes for the kill shot, guaranteeing he won't get hit, but it can also be said that he's losing mana efficiency on the kill shot nuke. <br>
<br>
My point of view is if I can learn something, i'm open to whatever sounds good, that's part of the fun of playing wizard.<br>
